com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor

Interface Functor<A>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - The type of the parameter
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CheckedFn1<A,B>, Fn1<A,B>, Fn2<A,B,C>, Fn3<A,B,C,D>, Lens<S,T,A,B>, Lens.Fixed<S,T,A,B,FT,FB>, Lens.Simple<S,A>, Lens.Simple.Fixed<S,A,FS,FA>, Predicate<A>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    All, Any, CartesianProduct, Const, Constantly, Cycle, Drop, DropWhile, Either, Filter, FoldLeft, FoldRight, Id, Identity, InGroupsOf, Iterate, Map, Over, Partial2, Partial3, ReduceLeft, ReduceRight, Repeat, Reverse, ScanLeft, Set, SingletonHList, Take, TakeWhile, Tuple2, Tuple3, Tuple4, Tuple5, Tupler2, Unfoldr, View, Zip, ZipWith
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Functor<A>
    An interface for the generic covariant functorial operation map over some parameter A. Functors are foundational to many of the classes provided by this library; generally, anything that can be thought of as "mappable" is an instance of at least this interface.

    For more information, read about Functors.

    See Also:
    Bifunctor, Profunctor, Fn1, Tuple2, Either
